requirement is:
Get tweets using twitter API or from a csv file having username, tweets and other data
analyse the sentiments using TextBlob
generate a graph using matplotlib

http://blog.aylien.com/first-text-mining-project-python-3-steps/
###############help file########################
usage: get_sentiments.py [-h] -f TWEET_FILE [-t TEXT] [-u USER]

Process some integers.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -f TWEET_FILE, -tweet_file TWEET_FILE
                        file having tweet info
  -t TEXT, -text TEXT   text about which sentiment data is required
  -u USER, -user USER   provide username to analyze data on user basis

####################################################
execution::
python get_sentiments.py  -f tweet_data.csv 
